Raveesh Kumar to be Foreign Ministry spokesperson.
Raveesh Kumar, a 1995-batch IFS officer who is currently posted in Frankfurt as Consul General of India, is understood to be the next spokesperson of the ministry of external affairs. Kumar will replace Gopal Baglay, who was on Friday appointed the joint secretary in the Prime Minister?s Office.The IFS?officer started his career at the Indian Mission in Jakarta. It was followed by a stint in Thimphu and London.During his previous tenure in Delhi, he looked after the East Asia desk.